0. APPROACH (why this is a COMBINED remaster, not a master pull)
---------------------------------------------------------------
- Analysed the source repo: 30 branches. Finding: `master` was already the
  integration branch — almost every feature/copilot branch (SEO, cookies,
  footers, mobile, loading, AI links) was MERGED into master with 0 unique
  commits ahead. Only Version-2.2 (5), improve-loading-screen-gui (1) and
  automated-ecosystems-designs-ionity (1) held anything master didn't.
- So "most weight" = master's distilled feature set, rebuilt clean. We kept the
  best DNA (dark immersive aesthetic, AI-welcoming robots.txt, real cookie
  consent, SEO/IndexNow groundwork, audio-manager concept) and re-authored it
  modular, unique and ~40x lighter — instead of carrying 119–314 KB monolith
  pages and 132 MB of assets.


1. BRAND / DESIGN
-----------------
- Extracted brand tokens from legacy style.css: #1A1A1A bg, #3366FF blue,
  cyan glow #00D2FF, white text, uppercase micro-labels, fixed glass nav,
  chevron scroll hints. Refined into a full token system (assets/css/ionity.css).
- NEW custom vector logo (ion-node motif, blue→cyan gradient): icon.svg, logo.svg,
  favicon.svg. Replaced the legacy 4800×3200 raster-in-SVG logos (1.5–7 MB each).
- Generated correctly-sized PWA icons (192/512/maskable/apple-touch) + a 1200×630
  OG social card via sharp. (Legacy "icon-192/512" were all the same 1.27 MB file.)


2. PAGES (immersive single-page adventure + lean supporting pages)
------------------------------------------------------------------
- index.html      — 9-act immersive scroll: Enter · Native-AI · Capabilities ·
                    Audit · Edge Scan (live) · RuView (live) · AEDi · Founder · Begin.
                    Scroll-rail, top progress bar, parallax orbital field, marquee,
                    count-up stats, reveal-on-scroll.
- services.html   — six disciplines EXPANDED and de-bulked (no tab overlap):
                    Native-AI & MCP · AIoT & Edge · Cloud & Digital Twins ·
                    Audit & Forensics · Hardware & Firmware · Custom B2B Systems.
- edge.html       — dedicated Edge Micro-Audit + RuView.
- about.html      — Antwerp Designs (2018) → Ionity arc, AEDi explained, founder
                    block with LinkedIn in/ionity + Gravatar antwerpdesigns.
- contact.html    — mailto form (no third-party tracker) + direct lines HUD.
- privacy.html / terms.html — real, plain-language legal incl. cookie + edge-scan
                    privacy statements.
- 404.html        — on-brand "off the grid".
- Page weight: 119–314 KB  →  9–28 KB each.


3. SIGNATURE FEATURE — EDGE MICRO-AUDIT (assets/js/edge-diagnostics.js)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
- 100% REAL, on-device, NO SIMULATION, nothing transmitted. Verified live in
  browser to read genuine values: GPU renderer (WebGL UNMASKED_RENDERER),
  CPU threads, deviceMemory, WebGPU availability, display + measured refresh Hz
  (from frame cadence), a real compute benchmark (Mops/s), MEASURED network RTT
  (5 real round-trips) + MEASURED throughput, battery, storage quota, platform,
  timezone — folded into an honest composite "Edge Readiness" index.

4. RUVIEW CONNECTOR (assets/js/ruview.js) — honoring "NO SIMULATIONS"
--------------------------------------------------------------------
- A browser is sandboxed and cannot scan a LAN / count nearby radios. RuView's
  Wi-Fi (CSI) sensing happens on Ionity HARDWARE. So the connector ONLY shows
  real data: connect a reachable RuView node (WebSocket or HTTP) and it streams
  live device/presence/motion; otherwise it shows a truthful "NO EDGE NODE"
  state. It NEVER fabricates a number. Verified: default state = "NO EDGE NODE / —".

5. AUDIO (assets/js/audio.js)
-----------------------------
- Procedural 8-bit INDUSTRIAL soundscape, fully synthesised with Web Audio API
  (no files): detuned square drones + LFO-swept filter + filtered noise "machine
  room" bed + periodic mechanical tick + chiptune hover/click/ok blips.
  Off by default; nav toggle; preference persisted; respects reduced-motion.

6. COOKIES / CONSENT (assets/js/cookies.js)
-------------------------------------------
- Granular opt-in manager: necessary (locked) · preferences · analytics ·
  marketing. Durable `ionity_consent` cookie (180d) + localStorage mirror.
  Fires `ionity:consent` for script gating. Re-openable via footer "Cookie
  settings". Verified accept/dismiss + cookie write.

7. SEO / AEO / PWA / TRUST
--------------------------
- Per-page <title>/description, canonical, OG + Twitter, theme-color, keywords.
- JSON-LD: Organization (+founder sameAs LinkedIn/Gravatar/GitHub), Breadcrumb,
  ContactPage.
- sitemap.xml, robots.txt (search + AI/answer engines explicitly allowed),
  llms.txt, humans.txt, security.txt + /.well-known/security.txt.
- manifest.json (standalone PWA, maskable icon, shortcuts), CNAME, .nojekyll.

8. ENGINEERING
--------------
- No framework, no runtime build. Deterministic static generator in _build/
  (layout.mjs = single source of truth for head/nav/footer/cookie/JSON-LD →
  guarantees consistent footers + links everywhere). HTML is committed; Pages
  serves the root directly. npm scripts: build · icons · serve · dev.

9. VERIFICATION (done, then re-checked)
---------------------------------------
- Static server smoke test: index/css/js/svg/services = 200, unknown = 404.
- Browser: home (desktop + 390px mobile) renders; no console errors.
- Edge scan executed live → real GPU/CPU/mem/refresh/RTT/throughput, score 99.
- RuView default = honest "NO EDGE NODE".
- Cookie accept writes consent + hides banner; persists on reload.
- Generator re-runs cleanly in repo layout.

